<h2>Salary</h2>

<p>Base pay starts at $30,000/year, with a raise to $36,000 after a 3
month probationary period. Let me explain that.</p>

<p>For the first 3 months, we will evaluate the fit to see if you are a
good match for this company. If either you or we decide that the fit
isn't right, we simply part ways.</p>

<p>On the other hand, if you are still with us at the end of the 3
months, you become a full-fledged, card-carrying Bigger Bird employee.
Congratulations! You get a guaranteed raise to $36,000, full benefits
(except for the retirement plan, which requires 1 year of service), and
enough business cards to last a lifetime. Further raises will be
performance based, with evaluations every 6 months. Bonuses may be
awarded for exceptional performance.</p>

<p>Now, we fully realize that this is pitiful, and we will work to fix
