<h2>Expected Qualities</h2>

<p>There are only three, and they are listed in order of importance.
Naturally, there are a lot of qualities we desire in an employee (you
know, the ones you always see... "team player," "excellent written and
verbal communications skills") but truly, if you have these three
qualities, you can do anything.</p>

<p><strong>Love of learning.</strong> You take a question you can't
answer or a task you've never attempted before as learning opportunity,
not a threat. There may be some fear of the unknown, but it is a
challenge, not a reason to give up or get defensive.</p>

<p><strong>Commitment to excellence.</strong> This is all about customer
service: having a friendly, can-do attitude. It doesn't mean you have to
be outgoing, but you must be able to receive requests or even complaints
with genuine concern for the client's needs and go the extra mile to
make sure the client is happy with the outcome.</p>

<p><strong>Attention to detail.</strong> There is a reason we all use
Macs as our primary machines: the littlest, seemingly insignificant
details, (often related to aesthetics or convenience), can make all the
difference. You need to at least appreciate this kind of quality or you
won't last long at our company.</p>


